# Coding Standards

## Formatting (enforced by Prettier)

- 4-space indentation (spaces, not tabs)
- Single quotes for strings
- Semicolons required
- Print width: 120 characters
- Trailing commas in ES5 positions (arrays, objects)
- Arrow functions: omit parens for single param (`x => x.foo`, not `(x) => x.foo`)
- Run `npm run format` before declaring work done

## Field Access

Always use `F.xxx(game)` from `src/lib/game-fields.js` for game field access:
- `F.theoWin(game)` — never `game.performance_theo_win`
- `F.provider(game)` — never `game.provider_studio`
- `F.themeConsolidated(game)` — never `game.theme_consolidated`
- `F.volatility(game)` — never `game.specs_volatility`

## HTML Security

All dynamic content in HTML templates must use sanitization:
- `escapeHtml(value)` for text content
- `escapeAttr(value)` for HTML attributes
- `safeOnclick('functionName', value)` for onclick handlers
- Never use raw string interpolation for user-visible content

## UI Patterns

### Tooltips
Use absolute positioning relative to the trigger, not `fixed`:
```
<div class="relative group">
  <button class="... cursor-help">?</button>
  <div class="hidden group-hover:block absolute left-full top-0 ml-1 w-60 ...">
    Tooltip content
  </div>
</div>
```

### Scroll Targets
Always scroll within `page-container`, never use `window.scrollTo` or `scrollIntoView`:
```js
const sc = document.getElementById('page-container');
const el = document.getElementById('target');
if (el && sc) { sc.scrollTop = el.offsetTop - sc.offsetTop - 8; }
```

### Panel Opening
When opening a side panel, call `window.closeAllPanels('panel-id')` with the panel's own ID to prevent race conditions.

## Testing

- Run `npm test` (vitest) before declaring any task done
- Run `npm run format:check` to verify formatting
- Coverage thresholds: branches >= 70%, functions >= 70%
- New UI features should have corresponding source-level validation tests
